{"NAKE":[{"def":"Come, be ready, nake your swords.","pos":"verb"}],"NAKED":[{"def":"Without pubescence; as, a naked leaf or stem; bare, or not covered by the customary parts, as a flower without a perianth, a stem without leaves, seeds without a pericarp, buds without bud scales.","pos":""},{"def":"Not having the full complement of tones; -- said of a chord of only two tones, which requires a third tone to be sounded with them to make the combination pleasing to the ear; as, a naked fourth or fifth.","pos":""}],"NAKEDLY":[{"def":"In a naked manner; without covering or disguise; manifestly; simply; barely.","pos":""}],"NAKEDNESS":[{"def":"The privy parts; the genitals.","pos":""}],"NAKER":[{"def":"A kind of kettledrum.","pos":""}]}